commitResults.messageTitle: Update storage to accommodate Order class
commitResults.messageBody:
After pulling the Order class from GitHub, multiple changes were made
to the storage files to integrate this new class and resolve associated issues.

Changes include:
- Added support for storing Order objects in storage interfaces
and implementations.
- Updated Storage interface to include methods for reading and
writing Order objects to files.
- Adjusted tests to reflect changes in storage functionality and
ensure proper handling of Order objects.

Additionally, several other adjustments were made across the
codebase to ensure consistency and maintainability.

This commit addresses the integration of the Order class into the
storage system, resolving related issues.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ViewOrdersCommand for displaying a list of orders
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit introduces the ViewOrdersCommand class, which represents a
command to display a list of orders. The allows users to view all
orders stored in the application.

The command provides functionality for retrieving and displaying all
orders in the system. It helps users quickly access and review the list
of orders without needing to specify any filtering criteria.

This commit adds ViewOrdersCommandTest to ensure the
ViewOrdersCommand properly displays all user orders as expected.
It verifies the correct handling and filtering of order data,
enhancing the reliability of the ViewOrdersCommand feature.

The Price threshold was above 0, meaning that orders could not be 0.
Additionally, the decimal places were not displayed to 2 decimal
places.

User's are confused and unable to give free orders to their loyal
customers, and their decimal points would not display properly.
Additionally, one user reported that not accepting 0 would crash the
application.

Fix the Price object by formatting it's toString method to format in 2
decimal places regardless of value, and allow 0 to be an accepted
value.

This will fix the users that the users experienced, and prevent the
application from crashing.
